  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Tear your <strong>bread roll[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add them to a baking tray, then sprinkle with your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Drizzle with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, mix it up and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the bread is golden and crunchy – these are your <strong>croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
